# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1) LET ACME-CHALLENGE PASS THROUGH (for Let’s Encrypt validation)
#    This tells Netlify: “If someone requests /.well-known/acme-challenge/ANYTHING 
#    on northbynature.uk or www.northbynature.uk, just serve it normally (200).”
/.well-known/acme-challenge/*   /.netlify/functions/:splat   200

# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 2) REDIRECT APEX (northbynature.uk) → WWW (www.northbynature.uk)
#    If host is exactly northbynature.uk (any path), send a 301 to https://www.northbynature.uk
https://northbynature.uk/*   https://www.northbynature.uk/:splat   301!

# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 3) ENFORCE HTTPS ON WWW
#    If someone comes in via HTTP (on either apex or www), push them to the HTTPS “www” version
http://www.northbynature.uk/*   https://www.northbynature.uk/:splat   301!
http://northbynature.uk/*       https://www.northbynature.uk/:splat   301!

# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 4) (Optional) You can add any other custom redirects below:
#    e.g. /old-path   /new-path   301
